M|rules|title: Prevent Waterfall Chains in API Routes
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: 2-10× improvement
M|rules|tags: api-routes, server-actions, waterfalls, parallelization
M|rules|In API routes and Server Actions, start independent operations immediately, even if you don't await them yet.
M|rules|**Incorrect (config waits for auth, data waits for both):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|rules|const ses = await auth()
M|rules|const config = await fetchConfig()
M|rules|const data = await fetchData(ses.user.id)
M|rules|return rsp.json({ data, config })
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (auth and config start immediately):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|rules|const sessionPromise = auth()
M|rules|const configPromise = fetchConfig()
M|rules|const ses = await sessionPromise
M|rules|const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
M|rules|configPromise,
M|rules|fetchData(ses.user.id)
M|rules|])
M|rules|return rsp.json({ data, config })
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|For operations with more complex dependency chains, use `better-all` to automatically maximize parallelism (see Dependency-Based Parallelization).